SimpleSetupGuide
1. Grab a Raspberry Pi. Anyone will do.
2. Flash Raspbian on SD-Card. I used the minimal version.
3. Boot the Pi. Do the network config. Do the raspi-config.
4. $_ sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade
5. $_ sudo apt install php5 apache2 php5-curl wiringpi
6. Copy all the files in htmlfiles to your htmldir
7. Copy twitter-php and all other files to your installdir
8. Make changes to your run.sh
9. Make changes to send.php
10. ....
11. PROFIT
